// Computing WCD bounds on a contended node, using residual service curves. 
// Requires the service curve to be \emph{strict}, see Secion 7.2.1 of https://doi.org/10.1002/9781119440284

// arrival curves for two traffic streams on the same node 
a1 := bucket(2, 2)
a2 := bucket(2, 2)
// *strict* service curve offered by the node to the aggregate traffic
sc := ratency(5, 1)
// residual service curve: what is offered by the node to a1, assuming a2 has first taken as much service as it can
rsc_1 := nnupclosure(sc - a2)
plot(out = "plot.png", a1, a2, sc, rsc_1)
hdev(a1, rsc_1)
